        "created_at": "2025-11-17T14:32:12.993Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Hi everyone,</p>\n<p>I’ve been using Signal for a while now and I’ve run into a practical issue: the app can get pretty heavy on storage over time.</p>\n<p>It would be incredibly helpful if Signal added a way to quickly see which chats are consuming the most disk space. Specifically, I’m looking for:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>\n<p>A “conversation size” view that shows the total storage each thread occupies, so I can spot the biggest culprits at a glance.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Sorting options that let me order my conversations by size, making it easy to prune or archive the largest ones.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Media‑size sorting within each chat (or globally), so I can identify the biggest photos, videos, or files and decide which to keep or delete.</p>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<p>Having these tools would let me keep Signal lightweight without accidentally losing important pictures or videos.</p>\n<p>Is anyone else interested in this feature?</p>",
